    {"clip_id":"q29","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"Santhosh left his stable bank job to become a wildlife photographer after spending years on the side. He recently returned from a six-week expedition in the Western Ghats and his photographs were featured in a national geography magazine.","questions":["What did Santhosh do before becoming a wildlife photographer?","How long was his expedition in the Western Ghats?"],"key_facts":[["bank job","banker"],["six weeks","six-week"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q30","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"The new traffic signal timing system introduced at five major junctions in the city uses sensor data to adjust green light duration based on live traffic flow. The pilot project will run for three months before a city-wide rollout.","questions":["What technology does the new traffic signal system use?","How long will the pilot project run?"],"key_facts":[["sensor","sensor data"],["three months"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q31","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"A local NGO has launched a programme to teach digital literacy to women above the age of fifty in rural areas. The classes are held three times a week at the village community hall and are completely free of charge.","questions":["Who is the digital literacy programme targeted at?","How often are the classes held?"],"key_facts":[["women","above fifty","rural"],["three times a week"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q32","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"The concert organised by the music school will be held at the open-air amphitheatre on the last Sunday of this month starting at six thirty in the evening. Entry is by invitation only, and tickets were distributed to students and their families last week.","questions":["Where will the concert be held?","Who received the tickets?"],"key_facts":[["amphitheatre"],["students","families"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q33","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"The water tanker that supplies drinking water to three colonies in the ward has been out of service for the past four days due to a pump failure. The corporation has arranged a temporary supply through private tankers until the vehicle is repaired.","questions":["Why has the water tanker been out of service?","What temporary arrangement has been made?"],"key_facts":[["pump failure"],["private tankers"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q34","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"Nithya has been shortlisted for a six-month fellowship programme at a research institute in Bengaluru. The fellowship covers accommodation, a monthly stipend of twenty-five thousand rupees, and access to the institute's laboratories.","questions":["Where is the fellowship programme located?","What does the fellowship include?"],"key_facts":[["Bengaluru"],["accommodation","stipend","twenty-five thousand","laboratory"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q35","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"A newly opened children's science museum in the city has interactive exhibits on topics such as space, the human body, and climate change. School groups can book guided tours on weekdays at a discounted group rate of forty rupees per student.","questions":["What topics do the museum's exhibits cover?","What is the group rate for school students?"],"key_facts":[["space","human body","climate"],["forty","40"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q36","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"The landlord of the commercial building has given tenants two weeks' notice to vacate the ground-floor shops due to renovation work. A few shopkeepers have been temporarily relocated to the adjacent lane.","questions":["Why have the ground-floor shopkeepers been asked to vacate?","Where have some shopkeepers been relocated?"],"key_facts":[["renovation"],["adjacent lane"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q37","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"The department store is running a clearance sale on winter clothing with discounts of up to sixty percent. The sale started on Monday and will continue until stocks last, with new items added every morning at nine.","questions":["What is the maximum discount offered in the clearance sale?","When does the store add new items?"],"key_facts":[["sixty percent","60"],["nine","every morning"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q38","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"Arjun had been practising for the state-level chess championship for nearly a year. He finally participated last month and reached the quarter-finals before losing to a former national champion. His coach says he will be ready for the nationals next year.","questions":["How long had Arjun been practising for the championship?","How far did he reach in the competition?"],"key_facts":[["nearly a year","one year"],["quarter-finals","quarterfinals"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q39","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"The school has introduced a five-day outdoor education camp for students in Grade Nine as part of the curriculum. The camp will be held at a nature reserve sixty kilometres from the city and will cover survival skills, teamwork, and wildlife awareness.","questions":["For which grade is the outdoor education camp?","Where will the camp be held?"],"key_facts":[["Grade Nine","Grade 9"],["nature reserve","sixty kilometres"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q40","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"A power cut lasting nearly four hours affected several parts of the western zone of the city yesterday evening. The electricity board confirmed that a high-tension wire had snapped near the sub-station and repairs were completed by midnight.","questions":["How long did the power cut last?","What caused the power cut?"],"key_facts":[["four hours"],["high-tension wire","snapped","wire"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q41","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"The new public library in the town square has a collection of over forty thousand books in six languages and also offers a children's section with illustrated story books and audio books. Membership is free for school and college students.","questions":["How many books does the library have?","Who gets free membership?"],"key_facts":[["forty thousand","40,000"],["school","college students"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q42","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"The company has decided to sponsor ten employees to pursue a part-time MBA programme at a recognised business school. Selected employees will have their tuition fees fully reimbursed and will be given flexible working hours on class days.","questions":["How many employees will be sponsored for the MBA?","What support will selected employees receive?"],"key_facts":[["ten","10"],["tuition fees","flexible hours"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q43","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"The heavy rain last Tuesday caused waterlogging on the main road outside the station, forcing commuters to wade through knee-deep water for nearly two hours. The drainage department cleared the blockage by early evening.","questions":["What caused the waterlogging on the main road?","How long did commuters face difficulty?"],"key_facts":[["heavy rain","rainfall"],["two hours","nearly two hours"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q44","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"The regional cooking festival held last weekend showcased dishes from twelve different states. Over three thousand visitors attended, and the stall representing Kerala won the best presentation award for the second year in a row.","questions":["How many states were represented at the cooking festival?","Which stall won the best presentation award?"],"key_facts":[["twelve","12"],["Kerala"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q45","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"The state government has announced free coaching for students from government schools who are preparing for engineering and medical entrance exams. The classes will be held on weekends at district headquarters and are open to students in Classes Eleven and Twelve.","questions":["For which exams is free coaching being offered?","When will the classes be held?"],"key_facts":[["engineering","medical entrance"],["weekends","Saturday","Sunday"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q46","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"An old building near the city centre that had been vacant for over twenty years is being converted into a heritage hotel. The renovation is expected to cost three crore rupees and the hotel is planned to open by the end of next year.","questions":["What is the old building being converted into?","What is the expected cost of renovation?"],"key_facts":[["heritage hotel"],["three crore"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q47","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"The office has implemented a new rule that all meetings must start and end on time, and no meeting should be scheduled for more than forty-five minutes without prior approval from the department head. The rule applies from this Monday.","questions":["What is the new rule regarding meetings?","From when does the rule apply?"],"key_facts":[["forty-five minutes","45 minutes","on time"],["this Monday","Monday"]]},
    {"clip_id":"q48","task_type":"QnA","reference_text":"A talented young artist from our city has won an international painting competition held in Paris, becoming the youngest Indian winner in the event's thirty-year history. She created a large canvas depicting the fishing community along the coast.","questions":["Where was the international painting competition held?","What was the subject of the winning painting?"],"key_facts":[["Paris"],["fishing community","coast","fishermen"]]},
